Author:  MORRIS
Vol / Page:  473
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Maori word for a wise man. `Perhaps from Maori verb tohu,</i> to think.' (Tregear's `Polynesian Dictionary.') <i>Tohu</i>, a sign or omen; hence <i>Tohunga</i>, a dealer in omens, an augur.
Notes:

