Source:  Maori Race, The
Author:  TREGEAR
Vol / Page:  20
Edition:
Quote:  ... it was for another, the wizard or priest <i>(tohunga)</i> to prescribe the remedy. <i>Ibid. 124 After these [sc. the chiefs] ranked the ordinary `professional' <i>(tohunga)</i> who though generally a priest or wizard needed not always to be a priest, but must be a `skilled person' either in witchcraft, canoe-making, house-building, tattooing, etc.
